# GEMINI

This file provides system/agent context for Antigravity AI pair programming sessions.

- **Codename**: XR_node / "Infinity Brain"
- **Architecture**: Flat, tag-based Zettelkasten.
- **Rule**: `02_NODES/` must remain completely flat with no subfolders.
- **Automations**: MOCs are rebuilt using `.antigravity/automations/generate_mocs.py`.

---

# System Enforcement

The Infinity Brain is a self-maintaining knowledge system. All policies described in this document should be enforced automatically through scripts, hooks, and agents.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Documentation is not the source of truth. **Automation is.**

---

# Single Sources of Truth

To prevent inconsistencies, rules must never be duplicated across multiple files. The system is defined by the following directory and schema files:

```
.antigravity/
├── rules/
│   ├── tag-schema.md          # All allowed tags
│   ├── promotion-rules.md     # Node promotion policy
│   ├── node-schema.md         # Atomic note structure
│   ├── moc-schema.md          # MOC structure
│   └── source-schema.md       # Source metadata
├── logs/
│   └── moc-health.md          # MOC and knowledge graph health reports
└── automations/               # Automation scripts
```

Whenever any of these schema files change, all automation must immediately adapt to follow the updated rules.

---

# Controlled Tag Schema

Tags are a strictly controlled vocabulary. **Never invent tags.** Every tag used in the vault must exist inside `.antigravity/rules/tag-schema.md`.

### Tag Categories

| Category           | Allowed Tags                                                                                                                          | Description / Rule                                                                          |
| :----------------- | :------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | :------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **Source**         | `#youtube`, `#podcast`, `#book`, `#article`, `#paper`, `#newletter`, `#substack`                                                      | Permanent source tags (`#youtube`, `#podcast`, `#book`, `#newletter) must never be removed. |
| **Knowledge Type** | `#concept`, `#fact`, `#principle`, `#framework`, `#workflow`, `#mental-model`, `#definition`, `#law`, `#question`, `#universal-truth` | Specifies the cognitive type of the note.                                                   |
| **Status**         | `#processed`, `#draft`, `#evergreen`                                                                                                  | The maturity/lifecycle stage of the note.                                                   |
| **Domain**         | `#ai`, `#ml`, `#psychology`, `#productivity`, ...                                                                                     | Subject area tags defined in the schema.                                                    |

---

# Duplicate Prevention

Before creating any node, check for existing knowledge to prevent redundancy:

1. **Search Title:** Find matching or synonymous note names.
2. **Search Aliases:** Check alternate names in note frontmatter.
3. **Search Semantic Similarity:** Scan for conceptually matching topics.
4. **Search Backlinks:** Check incoming references.

```
If equivalent node exists  ──► Update the existing node.
If partially related       ──► Create new node AND cross-link both.
```

> [!WARNING]
> Duplicate knowledge must never exist in the vault.

---

# Node Validation

Every atomic note in `02_NODES/` must satisfy the following checklist. Reject incomplete or non-compliant notes.

- [ ] **One Concept Only:** The note contains exactly one atomic concept.
- [ ] **MOC Association:** Belongs to at least one Map of Content (MOC).
- [ ] **Connected:** Has at least one backlink (incoming link).
- [ ] **Sourced:** Contains a valid reference to its source.
- [ ] **Valid Tags:** Contains only tags listed in `tag-schema.md`.
- [ ] **No Broken Links:** All internal links must resolve.

---

# Source Lifecycle

Raw files move through a structured ingestion pipeline. This process should be entirely automated.

```
 01_RAW/capture/ (Raw content captured by human)
       │
       ▼
 [Knowledge Ingestion]
       │
       ▼
 [Atomic Notes Created] (Written to 02_NODES/)
       │
       ▼
 [All Notes Linked] (MOCs rebuilt, notes cross-linked)
       │
       ▼
 01_RAW/source/ (Raw source file archived)
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Processed sources must never remain inside `01_RAW/capture/`. They must be moved to `01_RAW/source/` automatically upon successful ingestion.

---

# MOC Rules

- Every node must belong to at least one Map of Content (MOC).
- Nodes may belong to multiple MOCs.
- Orphan nodes are not allowed.
- Large MOCs should be split into domain-specific MOCs when navigation becomes difficult.

---

# Knowledge Graph Health & Reporting

After every MOC rebuild, the system automatically checks graph health and writes a report to `.antigravity/logs/moc-health.md`.

### Health Check Tasks
- **Orphan Detection:** Detects nodes with backlinks below the configured threshold.
- **Duplicate Detection:** Flags candidate duplicate concepts.
- **Broken Link Detection:** Identifies links pointing to non-existent files.
- **Invalid Tag Detection:** Flags tags not registered in `tag-schema.md`.
- **Empty MOC Detection:** Flags MOCs with no registered nodes.
- **Promotion Evaluation:** Evaluates candidate nodes for promotion.

### Orphan Mitigation
For every orphan detected, append details to `03_MOC/_orphans.md`:
- Title
- Backlink Count
- Suggested MOC
- Suggested Related Notes
- Suggested Merge Candidates

### Rebuild Log Metrics
The health report logs the following metrics:
- Date of check
- Node Count & MOC Count
- Orphan Count & Broken Link Count
- Duplicate Candidates
- Unknown Tags
- Average Backlinks per Node
- Largest MOCs & Fastest Growing Domains

---

# Promotion Rules

Promotion rules are defined only inside `.antigravity/rules/promotion-rules.md`. Automation should enforce them. Documentation should never be the enforcement mechanism.

---

# Quality Principles

- **Connection over Volume:** Better-connected knowledge is preferred over more knowledge. A vault containing 1,000 highly connected notes is superior to 10,000 isolated notes.
- **Automation over Memory:** Humans capture knowledge; automation maintains it. If a process is repeated more than once, it should eventually become automated.

---

# Success Criteria

The Infinity Brain is successful when:
1. Every source has been fully atomized.
2. Every node is discoverable through MOCs.
3. Every node is connected to related knowledge.
4. Every source is archived.
5. No duplicate concepts exist.
6. No invalid tags exist.
7. No orphan nodes remain unresolved.
8. Navigation never requires browsing folders.
9. The knowledge graph continuously improves with each ingestion.
